content.detailedDescription: It was round in shape with what appeared to be nodules all along the outside of the craft. we were coming home home from salem, where we had been shopping, my son and i that is, when we spotted it in the sky.  it followed us home and hovered over our house. i ran inside to get my new video camera and came back out and put the camera on my husbands truck to steady it and taped it for at least 5 minutes and then it seemed to turn and start to fade and then it just was gone.
content.flightPath: Hovering then path,Path with directional change,Path then hovering
content.summary: It was round with nodules around the outside.

content.detailedDescription: On febuary 11,  2009, while driving south on us interstate 93 around 130 miles north of phoenix i saw three orange spheres.  they would stay in mid air and disapear.  i was driving and noticed them though my winsheild. it was dark out and the moon had not yet risen.  it was around 8:00pm to 8:20pm.  i had pulled over on the side of the road to see if i could get a better look at the objects. at this point i knew i was not seeing any plane.  i had an intense feeling that i was vieving something not of this world.  i noticed an orange light much larger than any star in the sky and then one more. finnally there were three objects that where in the sky.  there was no sound or no flashing lights on the objects.  a few seconds watching ten and they were all gone.  i stayed parked on the side of the road to see if they would come back and about 5 minutes later they reapeared.  this continued for almost 3 hours.  i continued to watch the objects.  they stayed almost in the same spot of the sky as i watched.  they would dissaprear and reaprear 5 to ten miuntes later.  about 3 hours later i noticed them in another part of the sky.  this time there apeared to be more and more objects.  if i could give an estimate i would say there were about 30 of them in a cluster for about 20 seconds then they were all gone.  i decided that i needed to continue my drive back to phoenix as i did not see them again for over a half an hour.  as i got into cell phone rang i picked up my phone to call my family in new mexico to tell them of what i had seen.  i noticed the date on my phone was january 5,  2007 and the time was 4:19am.  i called my family and my phone kept changing time and turning on and off.  it took almost 3 more hours till my phone worked correctly.  i did check the time when i got home to tempe and it was 11:50pm.  i am still amazed at what i had seen.
content.summary: Three orange spheres.

content.detailedDescription:
I was working at a summer camp in 1999 in casar nc.  at this camp, there were many ufo sighting reported the previous summer, and some over the next two years as well.  
one day in june, my job required me to stay at the camp while all the staff and campers were out.  as i sat on the front step of the tool shed, 3 blacked out chinook helicopters buzzed the camp heading south, flying no more than 100 ft off the ground.  all 3 passed right over my head, so close i could see the pilot's faces.  besides scaring me a great deal, i thought it was incredibly odd, as there are no airfields of any kind near there.  
over the next many weeks that summer, myself and two co workers would sit on the front porch of the camp lodge late at night, looking east, and watch orange lights rise up, turn 90 degrees and once again head south.  no helicopter noise, and they had to be at least 3-5 miles away.  each night was the same occurence, and the lights would continue for at least 30 minutes each time. they were so far away we didn't feel scared. 
 casar is a perfect place for black ops, as it has a population of 398 and is very sparse and yet close enough to fly to from many metro areas.
many fellow staff people the summer before reported ufo sightings in the area as well, and the presence of the night stalkers there the following summer makes for an interesting connection.
content.summary: Night stalker helicopters near consistent sightings

content.detailedDescription:
I was sitting on my front porch and noticed a low star.I looked away for a few seconds.I looked back thinking that was not a typical part of the sky to see a star that bright.Then i thought it moved.I'm like did that thing just move? it did.I stared at it as it sort of slowly drifted about.It seemed to be west of me above mt.Madonna.I could not judge the distance.
i decided to get in my car to get a closer look.Half way up the mountain i could still see it through the trees.When i got there it was gone.
content.summary: I thought it was a star until it started drifting around.

content.detailedDescription: My sister and i, who were 10 and 13, respectively, were in my second floor bedroom in my house. we were looking out the window towards the north east. we saw a light in the sky in the distance. at the time we thought nothing of it because stewart international airport is in that direction and 747 planes take off and fly a route which goes over my house. a few planes had already passed before. this time was different. as the light approached it was much lower than the usual planes which by the time they are flying over the house, they are a few thousand feet in the air. this craft flew over the tree line slowly and then proceeded to fly over the roof of my house. i estimate it to have been about ten to fifteen feet above the roof. the craft was about thirty feet in diameter and was black. it had eight bright white lights on each of it's eight corners. the craft was an octagon shape. it rumbled very loudly. it did not shake the house nor did it produce wind as with a helicopter. i estimate it's speed at about five miles per hour. as it flew over the roof, my sister and i ran to the back of the house to watch it come over the roof but it never came. it was gone. immediately we ran down stairs to my mother. we asked her if she had just heard the very loud rumbling noise. there is no way she could not have heard it. she claimed that she hadn't heard anything. the last remembered time i noted was about 10:30pm. this was as the craft approached the house. i never checked the time after the event, which would have been vital had i known what "missing time" was. i believe though that my sister and i experienced "missing time". my theory is that the reason we did not see the craft come over the roof of the house from the back window is because it had passed and gone long before we ever ran to the back of the house to view it. additionally, my mother did not hear the craft, this is because a long time had passed since the craft actually flew over. these two things make me believe that several minutes or more had passed and the both of us (sister and me) didn't even notice, hence "missing time".
content.summary: Ufo flies over my house.

content.detailedDescription: I was on a sight-seeing trip when i stopped at a rest area to take the attached photo of the teton mountains.  at the time i took the photo, neither i nor my traveling partner noticed the ufo object.  i do not believe it was visible to the naked eye.  if it had been, we would have surely noticed it.  we were both facing the mountain range.  we did not hear any sounds either.  the photo was taken with a digital camera in mid-afternoon.  the sky was a little hazy and nearly cloudless.  i noticed the object in the photo after i returned home and was viewing the photos on my computer.
content.summary: Ufo near the grand teton mountains.

content.detailedDescription:
Prior to this date i have noticed lately an odd presence in our canadian skies particularly that over the ottawa valley. i was taking a stretch outside having a cigarette in my small rural town with very few lights to mask the skies with. since i was young i always had a stark interest in the skies above, especially at night, where its prime viewing where i live as its the highest point in the ottawa valley. i was walking along the street which has no street lights of any kind and i noticed a moderately bright light oscillating and changing colour.. red,green,gold,blue pulsating. to catch a better viewing angle there is a hill within a local park within walking distance of my house known as mckendry park. i stopped by my house picked up a pair of binoculars and thus proceeded to the point of interest. at first i was skeptical of even traveling to this place as it gives off some very eerie vibes and to make my paranoid self even worse there was clearly some sort of craft in the sky which i am supposed to believe is the work of pure science fiction the sort of stuff you see on the 6 o'clock news that your father has to mock in the close minded sense he lives in. i myself am respectably open minded seeker type so to speak, i attempt to wrap my mind around a lot of things people just disregard which is a waste of a life in all honesty especially in the times we live in now. i give my apologies in advance to those who just want some hard evidence and not a retrospective gonzo piece. i was standing on the top of a beast of a hill that was constructed to my understanding for kids to slide down in the winter its about a 50% grade.

 the sky was full of what looked like police cherries toned down except for one. i counted twenty-three and stopped so i could study the one that was the most intense, some of them were in a staggered line formation (i do have some military knowledge) i tried to work out possibilities in my head as to what they could be but really couldn't focus as i was always looking around at my environment not just the sky. i have read quite a few ufo accounts but i never felt that i would be writing one of these "ever" the lights were to the north-east and west just above ottawa. i could gauge that some were higher altitude than others due to light intensity. i figured it was probably military presence as barack obama was in ottawa the 19th. but this was not the first time i witnessed these lights, though not in this great number, during the month of february on a clear night one can look out their window if they're in the proximity of a suitable location and see what i have seen to some extent. for reference of time, first contact about 2:20am, on the hill roughly 3:15 due to the extremity of climate that i live in i was only there for about 30 minutes it was about -20 that night. i hope to see more accounts of activity over ottawa possibly on the news, though that usually turns out to be bad press so i doubt anytime soon though its a shame really i witnessed something amazing yet the only evidence is my word and i stand by it.
content.summary: Ufos over ottawa or ties with barack obama visit?

content.detailedDescription:
My younger brother and i (ages aprox 10 and 13) were upstairs in our home doing homework and our parents were downstairs watching television.  we had a large picture window on the back of the house and also a large picture window at the front of the house (bi-level home).  i happened to see a bright light out the back window...It appeared to be a mile or so away, not far above the trees moving too slowly to be a plane.  it was cigar shaped...Very bright.  at first i thought maybe a helicopter due to its slow steady movement.  i called my brother to the window.  as we watched the object moved from east to west over the tree line.  after a minute or so it began to move irratically...Up, down, side to side.  at this point we were pretty sure what we were seeing was not a helicopter but a ufo.  the object stopped in mid air...Then appeared to change shape into a cross and a light shot down from the object toward the ground.  my brother ran downstairs to alert my parents (they didn't believe him) and while he was down stairs the light zipped back up into the craft, it changed back to its original shape and then sped off so fast toward the west that i couldn't follow it...I ran to the front window but it was gone.  the entire sighting lasted about 10 to 15 minutes.   
around that same time period i also destinctly remember my dad coming home one evening after driving from his mother's house in southern michigan (aprox 30 minutes from our home) as white as a sheet.  he was visibly terrified.  my initial thought was he'd hit something or someone on the way home.  he proceeded to tell me that his van had been followed closely by a ufo...If he stopped, it stopped.  he said it was no more than a few feet above and behind him 1/2 way home.  i'd never seen my dad that frightened and i completely believed him.  he never mentioned it again.
content.flightPath: Path with directional change,Path then hovering
content.summary: Unusual ufo sighting

content.detailedDescription: Last evening 19/2/09 at 8:50 i was indoors watching television, with the sound turned up quite high. over the top of this i heard a very loud engine noise. thinking it might be a police helicopter on patrol overhead i went to the front door, which looks west. directly in front of me at 40 degrees elevation, i saw a red flashing light heading north. this light exhibited a completely irregular sequence of random blinks. the engine noise was now not as loud as i had initially experienced it, and appeared to be that of a single craft (no beat effect or audible interaction). immediately behind the random red light, at a distance of what i now estimate to be ten helicopter lengths, i saw a tight cluster of lights. comprising a red blinking beacon, white anti-collision strobe, and steady green starboard navigation lamp. the procession continued north at about 40 miles per hour. i deduce, from the volume of noise experienced, that a helicopter passed to the south of my house, heading east-west. then immediately turned in an arc toward the north. based on daily observation of numerous helicopter and aircraft types routing  into and out of the nearby military and civilian airports, the engine note was not one familiar to me. (the police usually deploy a eurocopter). but from visual and audible clues i estimate that the machine was at 150 feet, half the normal operating height in this area, due to a number of tall transmitter towers. if all the lights were on a single helicopter it would have had to have been chinook-sized, and about  50 yards from me. however, the sound was not that produced by this particular type, nor did i experience downwash. if the lights were on two separate craft then they were flying in a perilously low and close formation above a densely populated area. this 4i observation may or may not be of significance. (4i = insufficient information impedes identification). but i thought i would report it to you, as there have been incidents in wales, birmingham, and brighton. where constabulary aircraft have encountered/pursued/recorded anomalous aerial phenomena.
content.summary: Unusual event.

content.detailedDescription:
If you haven't heard of the "fireball(s)" that streaked over austin around noon on sunday, 2/15, then it's your lucky day. i was sleeping late on sunday when my bed lurched far enough above my bedroom floor to wake me up.  i sat upright and called for my wife.  she was downstairs in the kitchen when the "lurch" occurred and had lost her footing.  we have two dogs and they both freaked out when the "lurch" occurred and jumped over a 6ft fence and i've only found one of them.  all was quiet until around 4:00pm when continuous sonic-booms echoed over north central austin.  i thought i was hearing fireworks which is not unusual in my neck of the woods as some new shopping center is celebrating a grand opening weekly -- but the frequency and intensity of the reports -- not to mention the fact that they were happening in the clear light of day, struck me as odd.  

you can go to www.News8austin.Com and watch the video for yourself.  cnn has already purged it from their files which is odd as as they were the first to pick up the video and report it globally.

if you see a pug that answers to babette, please let me know.
content.summary: One of many.

content.detailedDescription: I was driving on newport ave and was looking toward 17th and noticed a very low star like object, it was really bright.  it wasn't a star.  i watched it for about 15 minutes.  it was there till i got to my destination.  when i got into my car around 10:00pm it was gone.  planes were flying around it like nothing was happening.  it was just sitting there motionless this is the second time i have seen this thing.  i want an explanation in what is going on.  is it a test aircraft or somthing else.  tomorrow i will get my cam corder ready in case i see this thing again.  it was not a sattlelite please help.  now i want to get into investigating these objects.
content.summary: It was as bright as as star.

content.detailedDescription: My brother came knocking frantically at my door saying he could see something strange out in the sky. we ran to the outside porch, from which we can see all of los angeles and the santa monica bay. directly over redondo beach and the bordering areas of palos verdes estates was a bright blue saucer-shaped object traveling incredibly quickly up and down, in loops, and back and forth, in a seemingly frantic mode. my brother thought it was a helicopter or plane, as we normally see these things, but its lights were incredibly bright, it made no noise, it was close, and it seemed to make movements otherwise believed to be aerially impossible. three of us saw this; my brother, myself, and my girlfriend. only my girlfriend was skeptical enough, in the end, to believe it was something man-made. she speculates that a local well-off individual has a new toy they were trying out. it seemed to be something more than that to my brother and i. we lost sight of the object when it disappeared into the woods near haggerty's, less than 100 yards from the pacific ocean.
content.summary: Bright blue lights travelling quickly from neighborhood streets up into the atmosphere.

content.detailedDescription:
on my lunch hour today i happened to be in my parked car laying back on the driver���s side and was leisurely gazing out the side window to the northeast.  i was watching one of the chemtrails generating from an aircraft that are so prolific in our area these days when i happened to spot a very tiny white dot in an otherwise clear blue sky.  my first reaction was that it was a high altitude weather balloon, but several things didn���t quite jibe with that.  	the location of the object seemed to be directly over denver international airport, but much higher than an airliner in that vicinity, and moving much too slowly for an ordinary aircraft. (it was definitely not a helicopter and this is the second time i have spotted a white morphing changing shaped white object in this vicinity over dia).
i had my variable powered binoculars with me, so i was able to get the object in view at 20 power.  it was very slowly drifting north , so i increased the power setting all the way to 80 power.  what i saw was quite strange.  it was basically a white spherical object that seemed to be changing shape, and perhaps rotating, and continuously morphing into an oblong shape and then back into a sphere about every second or two.  i watched this object for about 5 minutes and realized it was moving against the prevailing surface wind and seemed very high up.  while the object was in view, i was startled by the appearance of another dark object that zipped by so fast in the field of view that i could not tell what it was.  (slim chance it was a bird, but i got the feeling that it may not have been).  i also noticed a kind of glowing mist surrounding the white object, and what appeared to be a dark surface circle embedded in the middle of the white object that reminded me of a bathysphere like appearance.  i am reporting this event because of the strange morphing and changing shape plus the somewhat glowing mist like appearance surrounding the object.  if anyone knows what this tiny white sphere like object changing shape with a surrounding mist could be other than a high altitude weather balloon or a true ufo, please respond.  i will be watching the 20 latest reported sightings for the next few days.  thank you.
content.summary: Small white sphere changing shape with glowing mist surrounding it.

content.detailedDescription:
i was traveling in the car on the way to perkins restaurant for coffee, going north on roosevelt avenue near the high school, and i glanced up at the sky at 6:07 a. m. i noticed a brilliant blue light in the southeast. as it came nearer, i could see an oval-shaped craft about 50 feet long and 40 feet wide with a blue light on the bottom and cruising about 400-500 feet above the ground. it had no identifying marks, no wings, and no propellers, and no means of propulsion such as rockets or jets. i thought it must be some sort of an anti-gravity device, and i realized it must be a ufo, since i have seen one before. i only got a glimpse of it for about four seconds, and it shot off fast in a northwest direction. it descended slightly, and i could see a dark gray checkered top. then it curved west and took off in the direction of the iowa army ammunition plant. my state of mind before the event was calm, but afterwards i was very interested and excited.
i lost sight of the object since it went over the horizon. there was no sound.
content.flightPath: Hovering then path,Path with directional change
content.summary: Egg-shaped object, blue underneath, black checkered on top

content.detailedDescription: On the night of the sighting, i was out on my deck looking to the northeast. that is when i seen this object suddenly, appear out of the sky dropping its altitude so fast the the amount of g forces would have killed a human, then it came to a complete stop at around 800 ft(hard to tell how high it was and how far) above ground, and just as fast as it had stopped it shot off to the east. what baffels me is that there was no sound and how fast it moved. i just wish there was someone who seen what i seen that night
content.summary: Falling object stops, makes 90 degree turn then moves again.

content.detailedDescription: Okay, i was going to school with my mother, and i saw what appeared to be a round-topped, teardrop-traingle craft, it was red all over, flew aross the road and stopped. when it stopped, it jerked a little. in fact, when i saw it come in and out of view, it phased. i wasn't scared when i saw it, or after i saw it.
content.summary: It looked like it was red, red all over, with what appeared to be a black front and an up-side down v wing in back.

content.detailedDescription: I took my dog outside and noticed a glowing object in the western sky between the trees. i walked to the top of my driveway where there is a clearing to get a better look. there were no clouds in the sky, it was a clear night with a good view of the stars. i live quite a few miles out of town so it was very dark out. at first i thought that it was a planet. it appeared to be a vertical bright white light, cylindrical in shape, with a red light on the top and bottom of the object. there were two triangular blue wing-like outlines on each side of the object. the object would dim almost to the point of darkness and then glow really bright as if it were made of neon lights. the object seemed to lose altitude slowly and then rise several degrees as if it were a kite in the breeze. i observed the object for over an hour off and on, between tending for the dog, looking for my 35mm camera with a telephoto lens (which i couldn't find) calling friends to see if they could see it, and trying to stay warm. (it was about twenty degrees out) i even drove toward several miles down the road toward it to see if it got bigger or smaller, but it remained the same size. i finally gave up, going back into the house. i did peek out several times during the next half hour, and then it was gone. i tried to take a picture with my digital camera, but to no avail. i am an artist with a knack for detail so i made up a computer sketch to show what it looked like. the colors are not accurate, the true colors on the object were neon-like and very bright. i really would like to believe that it was a planet, but i don't know how a planet could look like that.
content.summary: Appeared in the western sky aprox. 15-20 degrees above horizon.

content.detailedDescription: I was traveling to st.George utah on the morning of dec.04,2007.I left kingman,az. at approx.2:10am.I was heading north on hiway 93 towards las vegas at approx.M.P.40 and approx.2:45am when the entire sky lit up above me.There had only been 2 other vehicles that i passed(they were heading south),and there was no traffic in front of me for at least10 miles.When the event happened i was traveling at 70 mph and immeadiately let off the gas and started slowing down.Hiway 93 runs thru the center of a long valley for close to 50 miles and is 20 miles across in places.At mp40 it is about 15 or 16 miles wide from peak to peak.I remember the sky lighting  up so bright that i could see details in the landscape of the hills.Also there is a towing yard in this area and i could tell the colors on the parked vehicles.I tried to look out the window of my truck up towards the sky above me.Then i saw a large green fireball streaking towards the ground from the south to the north at about a 45 degree angle.I estimate at 200 to 500 ft it broke up into several dozen orange colored fragments some of which i believe hit the ground.(i did a quick search of the area a few days later but found nothing.)i stopped my truck,got out and walked around for a bit but the event was over,lasting about 7 or 8 seconds.Thirty miles up the road there is a police check point before crossing hoover dam,where they stop traffic and perform vehicle inspections.When i stopped they immeadiately asked me if i had seen the bright flash in the sky.They stated it lit up the entire southern hemisphere from there viewpoint.A friend was also traveling towards kingman at the same time only he was about 140 miles east(around flagstaff,az.),and he saw the western sky light up and assumed it might be lightning although there was only high thin clouds at the time.I dont know what it was that was above me but ihave to assume it was quite large and that it violently exploded some how up above me.I feel the green fireball and the fragments were just a small part of the event that took place that morning.It had to be quite large to be seen from 140 miles away.
content.summary: Entire sky lit up above me then a green fireball shot down towards the ground which broke up into several dozen pieces

content.detailedDescription: I was camping at muskallonge lake state park on the shores of lake superior. it was labor day weekend, 1991.  i remember the year because my son was 14 years old at the time, however, i don't remember the exact day of the weekend. we walked from our campground over the sand dunes and down to the beach at approximately 11:00 pm because we wanted to see the northern lights.  as we were sitting there talking, we looked out over the horizon of the lake and saw what looked like lighted sails on a sailboat.  the colors were bright yellow and orange.  it was so far in the distance that i thought it was sailboats (there were 3 or 4), but, my friend said, "sails are not a solid light like that."  we began watching them and it appeared that they were moving closer....Coming towards shore, but they were still very far off in the distance.  as they appeared to move closer, i started getting a little nervous feeling and told my friend, "let's go."  then, before our eyes, they turned white, turned into circles and shot straight up and disappeared.  this has always stayed extremely vivid through the years, but i have shared it with few people. i have tried googling the info to see if anyone else saw the same thing that weekend, but couldn't find anything. i would be very curious if anyone else saw the same thing on and over lake superior around that time or anytime since.
content.summary: Bright triangle shapes appeared to be sailboats in the distance on lake superior, then turned into circles and shot up into sky.

content.detailedDescription:
Myself, and a friend had stepped outside for a cigarette while visiting my grandparents at their country home. there were meteor showers that night, and conditions were excellent for star gazing. i noticed two high altitude crafts traveling from north to south very slowly. i pointed them out to my friend and we both continued to watch them. we ruled out that they were not planes ( public or commercial ) due to the lack of blinking emergency lights that you can see at night. they were so distantly upward and bright that i began to think they must be satelites. it was just too strange though. they were about a half inch apart in the sky, one following the other, and zig-zagged completely in sync with eachother in their southward heading. i then consulted with my friend and we ruled out satelites as being what we were observing. they definatly must be piloted aircraft we thought. now my father is a pilot, and i had co-piloted with him on many occasions at dusk, and night.          
i was quite used to spotting air traffic and could tell these were unique given there precise cordination. we watched the two crafts for close to ten minutes when suddenly they both faded upward, as if dissapearing into the distance, but in space. we both stood there looking upward stunned and dumb-founded. i concluded at that point we must have wittnessed some form of military expieramental aircraft. wow! (the nearest military instillation being ft. hood some 80 miles away). we both continued to watch the sky hoping for another glimpse. suddenly there is a brilliant flash, very much like a camera flash going off on the other side of a stadium. this was near where the first two craft had vanished. i had never seen, heard, or been educated about anything like this flash before. perhaps an explosion? so now we were set on observing the sky. this is where it gets freaky. i was in no way prepared for what we see next. my grandmother's home is the flightpath of incoming and outgoing dfw traffic. there was a northbound 747 passenger airline. we could not help but to track it too since it was in the same vicinity of sky we were already watching. suddenly there was a very large, and bright star-like orb directly tailing the plane. my stomach literaly sank. i feared that this thing was going to harm the airliner. it followed the plane for nearly five minutes, matching the planes airspeed and appeared to be at just a slightly higher altitude. it then sped up to the plane at intense speed and vanished over the tail section of the plane. at this very moment another one of these objects appears from the same spot as where the object we had just seen vanished, first appeared. it shot directly over our heads, causing me to fall backwards. it simply vanished overhead. i was in a state of shock. these things had interacted with a passanger jet and now with us. about an hour later, at sunrise, my friend says he watched a star i had also observed, just after i had gone inside to wake up my family and scan the news channels for any coverage, vanish. in his own words it was as if a light was just switched off. the star was brilliantly bright, producing the same amount of light as the morning star. i went outside, it was still twilight ; the star, gone. i am a first responder in the state of california, a volunteer cival air patrolman, and another observer of the real unknown. i've expierianced near post dramatic stress symptoms since the sighting. i believe that at this time, on this planet, we ( humans ) do not possess the flight computer tecknology, propulsion, or ability to create the appearance these things had. hope this helps somehow, and good look to those still hoping to have the truth revealed.
content.summary: Aereal phenomenon; 4 definitive ufos, bright flash, and a dissapearing star.
